## When This Workflow Triggers

| Source Workflow | Trigger Point |
|---|---|
| **0a** (Setup) | After Phase 7 component tests |
| **0b** (Add Component) | After Steps 4 and 5 (test execution) |
| **0c** (Fix/Update) | After Steps 2A, 4, or 5 (re-run/verify) |
| **0e** (Config Update) | After verification tests |
| **Direct test run** | Any manual `test-storybook` execution |

---

## Cumulative HTML Report Behavior

When multiple components are tested across sessions:

1. **First component:** Creates `storybook-test-report.html` with one tab
2. **Second component:** Reads existing HTML, adds second tab, updates summary totals
3. **Re-test same component:** Replaces that component's section with fresh data
4. **Summary cards:** Always show aggregate totals across ALL tested components

---

## Existing Report Reference

The current `test-results/storybook-test-report.html` uses the Accordion component data as the baseline. Use it as the reference for styling, layout, and structure when generating reports for additional components.

